item.title: Port Forwarding
item.dc:creator: @icauseownage icauseownage
item.description:
@icauseownage wrote:

The computer on the bottom right hand corner double click it, look up at the tabs, click the tab ‘support’ and look at your ip address AND your default gateway, write them down on notepad. go to your internet explorer browser type in the DEFAULT GATEWAY. and depending on your router you would log, with those credentials. (unless it’s been changed) then find something about portforwarding (my router says it clear enough “port forwarding” lol) and put in like i said before.

btw yeah hamachi is easier and plus i can run it from this computer 4gb of memory =) :D[br][size=1]Posted on: March 31, 2007, 10:24:25 AM[/size][hr][quote=“Brad_c, post:21, topic:72588”]bleh, il stick with ham, im on a wireless connection ad that would explain it not working…
